    "NoisyS tudentDue to the scarcity of labeled faulty data, Unsupervised Learning (UL) methods have gained significant traction for detecting and localizing anomalies in NFV systems.",
    "In a UL approach, training is exclusively conducted on normal data to learn normal data patterns, and any deviation from the norm is considered an anomaly.",
    "However, it has been demonstrated that even small percentages of anomalous samples in the training data can substantially degrade the performance of UL methods.",
    "To address this issue, the aurhors of [79] proposed an anomaly detection approach based on the technique, initially introduced to leverage unlabeled datasets in computer vision classification problems.",
